                <h1>Understanding Divine Mercy: A Deep Dive</h1>
                <p>Divine Mercy is a Christian devotion rooted in the teachings of Saint Faustina Kowalska, a Polish nun who experienced visions of Jesus in the 1930s. It emphasizes God's boundless mercy and love, encouraging believers to trust in Him and seek forgiveness. The Divine Mercy image and the Chaplet are key elements of this devotion, celebrated on Divine Mercy Sunday.</p>
